{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.onSet\"><span class=\"name\">IO</span>.<span class=\"name\">CancelToken</span>.<span class=\"name\">onSet</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">tk</span> : <a href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\">CancelToken</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">action</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Registers a callback to run when the cancellation token is set or dropped. The callback runs as a\nsynchronous task dependency, so it executes inline on the thread that calls `set` (or on the\nfinalizer thread if the token is dropped). If the token is already set when `onSet` is called,\nthe callback runs immediately.\n","docLink":"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.onSet","kind":"def","line":68,"name":"IO.CancelToken.onSet","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/System/CancelToken.lean#L68-L75"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.isSet\"><span class=\"name\">IO</span>.<span class=\"name\">CancelToken</span>.<span class=\"name\">isSet</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">tk</span> : <a href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\">CancelToken</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Checks whether the cancellation token has been activated. ","docLink":"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.isSet","kind":"def","line":64,"name":"IO.CancelToken.isSet","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/System/CancelToken.lean#L64-L66"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.set\"><span class=\"name\">IO</span>.<span class=\"name\">CancelToken</span>.<span class=\"name\">set</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">tk</span> : <a href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\">CancelToken</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Activates a cancellation token. Idempotent.\n\nResolves the underlying promise *before* setting the `Bool` flag, so that observing `isSet = true`\nimplies that any synchronously-chained `onSet` callbacks have already run. The reverse implication\ndoes not hold: a callback running synchronously inside `set` may briefly observe `isSet = false`.\n","docLink":"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.set","kind":"def","line":53,"name":"IO.CancelToken.set","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/System/CancelToken.lean#L53-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.new\"><span class=\"name\">IO</span>.<span class=\"name\">CancelToken</span>.<span class=\"name\">new</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\">CancelToken</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates a new cancellation token.\n\nNote: cannot be called from `initialize` blocks because the underlying task manager is not yet\nrunning at that point. Construct lazily on first use instead.\n","docLink":"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken.new","kind":"def","line":42,"name":"IO.CancelToken.new","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/System/CancelToken.lean#L42-L51"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.instNonemptyCancelToken\"><span class=\"name\">IO</span>.<span class=\"name\">instNonemptyCancelToken</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nonempty\">Nonempty</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\">CancelToken</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.instNonemptyCancelToken","kind":"instance","line":38,"name":"IO.instNonemptyCancelToken","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/System/CancelToken.lean#L38-L38"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\"><span class=\"name\">IO</span>.<span class=\"name\">CancelToken</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Cancellation token for cooperative task cancellation: request cancellation with\n`CancelToken.set` and check for it with `CancelToken.isSet`. To react to cancellation without\npolling, register a callback with `CancelToken.onSet`.\n\nThis is a more flexible alternative to `Task.cancel` as the token can be shared between multiple\ntasks.\n\nNote: the underlying `Promise` and the task it produces are kept private. If a future change\nexposes the underlying task (or the promise) publicly, the `set` implementation must be\naudited for races between resolving the promise and writing `setRef`: callers observing\n`isSet = true` and then waiting on the task currently rely on the order chosen in `set`, and\nthat ordering interacts with the cheap `Bool` fast path read by the C++ runtime.\n","docLink":"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken","kind":"structure","line":17,"name":"IO.CancelToken","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/System/CancelToken.lean#L17-L38"}}],"imports":["Init.System.Promise"],"instances":[{"className":"Nonempty","name":"IO.instNonemptyCancelToken","typeNames":["IO.CancelToken"]}],"name":"Init.System.CancelToken"}